The paper discusses a method for digital identity verification using blockchain technology, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of zero-knowledge proofs and Merkle trees suggests a focus on cryptography (cs.CY) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The mention of controlling user data and enforcing confidentiality suggests a focus on databases (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE).
